From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: pidfd_getfd: add PTRACE_MODE_GETFD for fine-grained access control

Add PTRACE_MODE_GETFD flag (0x20) so LSMs can distinguish fd
extraction (pidfd_getfd) from full ptrace attach. KACS maps these
to different process SD access rights:
  - PTRACE_MODE_ATTACH → PROCESS_VM_WRITE (0x0020)
  - PTRACE_MODE_GETFD  → PROCESS_DUP_HANDLE (0x0040)

This allows administrators to grant fd extraction without granting
full debugging access via process Security Descriptors.

--- a/include/linux/ptrace.h
+++ b/include/linux/ptrace.h
@@ -64,6 +64,7 @@
 #define PTRACE_MODE_NOAUDIT	0x04
 #define PTRACE_MODE_FSCREDS	0x08
 #define PTRACE_MODE_REALCREDS	0x10
+#define PTRACE_MODE_GETFD	0x20

 /* shorthands for READ/ATTACH and FSCREDS/REALCREDS: */
 #define PTRACE_MODE_READ_FSCREDS (PTRACE_MODE_READ | PTRACE_MODE_FSCREDS)
--- a/kernel/pid.c
+++ b/kernel/pid.c
@@ -836,7 +836,7 @@
 	if (ret)
 		return ERR_PTR(ret);

-	if (ptrace_may_access(task, PTRACE_MODE_ATTACH_REALCREDS))
+	if (ptrace_may_access(task, PTRACE_MODE_ATTACH_REALCREDS | PTRACE_MODE_GETFD))
 		file = fget_task(task, fd);
 	else
 		file = ERR_PTR(-EPERM);
